<section class="leading-articles">
			<article class="article 0 clearfix">
			
<header>
	<h1>
					Our Water, Our Life: The Future is Blue			</h1>
</header>    





<section class="article-intro">

<p><strong>Photography Exhibit</strong></p>
<p><a href="/images/Our_Water_the_Future_is_Blue_Poster.pdf" target="_blank">Our Water Our Life: The Future is Blue</a></p>
<p><br />Water is central to the beauty we enjoy on Earth, gives life to all sentient beings, and is key in the production of things we use everyday.</p>
<p>DesBrisay Museum is pleased be a partner in presenting&nbsp;this photography exhibit to raise awareness and create dialogue to help enhance the appreciation, conservation, and protection of our water commons.</p>
<p>Visit the Facebook Page at <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/165499777161724/">https://www.facebook.com/groups/165499777161724/</a>&nbsp;</p>
<p>To view&nbsp;a small sampling and story cards from last year's exhibit, go to <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/136307696@N07/">https://www.flickr.com/photos/136307696@N07/</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</section>


		</article>
			</section>

<section class="intro-articles">
		
		<article class="items-row cols-2 row-0 clearfix">
					<div class="item column-1">
				
<header>
	<h1>
					Facebook and Genealogy 			</h1>
</header>    





<section class="article-intro">

<p><img style="margin: 5px;" src="/images/facebook_and_genealogy.png" alt="facebook and genealogy" width="500" height="222" /><br />You may be familiar with Facebook for chatting with friends or sharing your holiday pictures, or you may be steering clear thinking it's not for you.</p>
<p><strong>But have you considered how Facebook can work for genealogy research?</strong></p>
<p>Pamela Wile of the Genealogical Association of Nova Scotia will help you make Facebook part of your genealogy toolbox. And during the session, she will touch on a few other social media applications that are helpful as well</p>
<p>Saturday, May 7, 1-4pm<br />DesBrisay Museum<br />$15 admission</p>
<p>Advance Registration is Required – Call 902-543-4033 or email 
